<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Lynet on 05-02-2001 10:19 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">As a practical matter, anything they choose for a BOTB tourney has to have matches that take just a few minutes, 3 to 5 seems best.

I watched the Ranger BOTB tourney on E'ci and they ran through 15 contestants in just a couple of hours.  

The thought of 2 clerics, with maces and furor, swinging at one another and then completely healing themselves.  Well, it makes me tremble.  Those matches would last forever.

Even the wave of undead would have to be something that comes on fast.  Perhaps if they made a list of all the undead, in increasing order of nastiness, and popped them seriatum every 20 seconds in the middle of the arena until the cleric dies or 5 minutes elapse.  The winner kills the most undeads in that time.

I can keep a group going for a LONG time against tough odds, so that notion would not work so well.

My other thought would be to give each cleric a suit of sentient armor.  The suits would start next to one another and aggro on each other - they would fight as NPC's but could be buffed and healed.  Then clerics would have to choose between healing their champion, nuking the other champion, or disrupting the other healer.  That might lead to some interesting fights.

Lynet Beaumains, The Damosel Savage</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
